cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DM, cs.CL, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the semantics of logic programs with negation and boolean context-free grammars.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a new fixed point operation for non-monotonic functions, which is relevant to programming language semantics.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with complete lattices and fixed point operations, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper discusses the semantics of boolean context-free grammars, which are used in natural language processing.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the semantics of grammars and fixed point operations, which are topics in formal languages and automata theory.
